name: 16k Superchess
summary: A chess game from Chris Whittington.

name: 16bit Trader
summary: Take revenge on your father’s killer!

name: 16 Bit Arena
summary: It's time for a 16-bit beatdown! Enjoy the Card Game, Trials, chatting, and rockin' to some awesome music as you fight in retro-style battles up to 9v9!

name: 16 Tiles Mahjong
summary: 16 Tiles Mahjong is a Board game, developed by City Man Technologies and published by Sun Green Technology, which was released in Asia in 1992.

name: 16 Ways to Kill a Vampire at McDonalds
summary:
You're a vampire hunter on your night off.

You're getting a manicure, seeing a movie, and eating fast food.

But there's a vampire in this McDonalds.

If you don't do something, then in one hour it will eat the cashier.

name: 16t
summary: Players control a convict who fights monsters with heavy weights.

name: 16 Shot! Shooting Watch
summary: 16 Shot! SHOOTING WATCH is an enhanced and portable version of the original Shooting Watch, which was released by Hudson Soft in 1987.

name: 16 Shot! Shooting Watch
summary: Back in the 8-bit glory days, Hudson's own "Master Higgins" (a.k.a. Takahashi Meijin) made a splash in the gaming world with his astonishing trigger-finger speed of 16 shots per second. Can you break the Master's record?

name: 16bit-Collection Data East Vol. 03
summary:
This release contains the following games in a single cartridge:

Tatakae Genshijin 3 : Shuyaku wa yappari Joe & Mac (Joe & Mac 2: Lost in the Tropics)
Magical Drop 2
Side Pocket
All games are in their original Japanese language.

name: 16bit-Collection Culture Brain Vol. 02
summary:
Three additional Culture Brain classics for Super Famicom.

Included on this cartridge:

Super Chinese World 2
Super Ultra Baseball 2
Hiryu no Ken S: Hyper Version

name: 16bit-Collection Culture Brain Vol. 03
summary:
Three more Culture Brain Classics for the Super Famicom.

Included on this cartridge:

Super Chinese World 3
Super Chinese Fighter
SD Hiryu no Ken

name: 16bit-Collection Athena Vol. 01
summary:
16bit-Collection Athena Vol.1 is a 16-bit cartridge which built 5 titles in one cassette of old masterpiece game.

Includes:
- Pro Mahjong Kiwame
- Pro Mahjong Kiwame 2
- Pro Mahjong Kiwame 3
- Dezaemon SFC
- Biometal

name: 16bit-Collection Data East Vol. 1
summary:
Four Data East classics on one cartridge for Super Famicom.

Included on this cartridge:

Magical Drop (known as Chain Reaction in the West)
Joe & Mac
Fighter's History
Motteke Oh! Dorobou

name: 16bit-Collection Culture Brain Vol. 01
summary:
Three Culture Brain Super Famicom classics on one cartridge.

Included on this cartridge:

Super Chinese World
Super Ultra Baseball
Hiryu no Ken S: Golden Fighter

name: 16bit-Collection Data East Vol. 02
summary:
Three additional Data East games compiled together for the Super Famicom.

Included on this cartridge:

Fighter's History: Mizoguchi Kiki Ippatsu!! (known as Fighter's History 2 in the West)
Tatakae Genshijin 2: Rookie no Bouken (known as Congo's Caper in the West)
Super Birdie Rush

name: 16bit-Collection Jaleco Vol. 01
summary:
A collection of five Jaleco titles for Super Famicom.

Included on this cartridge:

Rushing Beat Ran: Fukusei Toshi
Rushing Beat Shura
Fire Fighting
Ikari no Yōsai
Super E.D.F.

name: 16 Planes:Return
summary: When you feel like you have slept for a long time and suddenly wake up to find that the world has changed and you have grown into middle age, who is the first person you think of as your closest relative?

name: 16 Zhang Mahjong
summary: 16 Zhang Mahjong (十六張麻將) is one of several unlicensed pornographic mahjong games for the Sega Mega Drive, developed by Gamtec

name: 16 Zhang Mahjong II
summary: 16 Zhang Mahjong II (十六張麻將 II) is an unlicensed pornographic mahjong game for the Sega Mega Drive. It is the sequel to 16 Zhang Mahjong.

name: 16-Bit Xmas 2011
summary: Gather up all of your best friends for the first SNES homebrew game by RetroZone, Christmas Craze, written by Shiru. Dodge aliens and grab gifts or fight your friends with snowballs in two player present picking battles. While everyone is drunk on egg nog trip out to the colorful blinky lights that surround the edge of the cart! When you gather presents in the game the lights dance with the sound effects.

name: 16 Tales: Vol. 2
summary: 16 Tales is a series of educational video games developed by The Lightspan Partnership starting in 1996. Each game consists of four 15-minute video programs detailing various cultures' stories and lore.

name: 16-Bit Soccer
summary:
Do you love those soccer games on consoles & home computers from the 90s?

If you want to relive those moments of fast-paced action with cool pixel graphics then "16-Bit Soccer" is just what you're looking for!

You'll get a real buzz playing this game which is easy to learn but hard to master and even more difficult to put down!!!

name: 16bit vs. Reality
summary: Retro-style platformer inspired by the 16bit classics. Jump and shoot your way through challenging levels. Watch two distinct visual styles collide. Enjoy the awesome rocking music. In the name of all that is childhood!

name: 16 Greens
summary: A bog standard minigolf game with 4-player pass-and-play multiplayer

name: 16 Bit Rally
summary:
Revisit the good old days of arcade racers with 16 Bit Rally, developed by Photon Creations.

Race on tracks all around the world, through some of the harshest and picturesque environments against 19 other competitors all aiming for the prized 16 Bit Cup.
Earn prize money from races, purchase car upgrades & new car models, gaining that edge over the competition.

Psychedelic 3D maze-runner. Each level is more difficult than the last one. Fight an onslaught of enemies as you try to find your way to the center of the island. You play as a revenant, avenging your death, and trying to free your sister from prison.

name: 16Bit Rhythm Land
summary:
This product is a 16-bit game cassette that lets you enjoy in Mega Drive. The 16Bit Rhythm Land incorporates FM sound source widely used in games and PC. In four built-in games, a total of 20 songs are recorded. The specialist of the FM sound source who worked on the songs focused on the legend game music world is called to be the heart of this rhythm game!

Furthermore, the design of the package is drawn by a designer who has done famous games! The 16-bit music rhythm game is also recommended for FM sound source fans.

name: 16 Balls: Pocket PachinGo!
summary:
16 Balls Pocket Pachingo will test your skill and luck to hit all the 16 lights or form patterns to get bonuses! How much can you push your luck to get big epic winnings?!
The game lets you play as Benjo who secretly adores a sweet girl named Michelle a frequent visitor of the local arcade. Benjo noticed Michelle's adoration of stuff toys. Benjo happens to be a master of 16 Balls Bingo Pachinko game where you can convert your winnings to cute stuff toys ranging from Bears to Turtles to Penguins. He saw an opportunity to bag all prizes and strike a conversation with his crush! Can you do it?!

name: 1630: The Thirty Years' War
summary: 1630: The Thirty Years' War is a thrilling and immersive real-time strategy game. Experience one of the most tumultuous periods in European history, using your strategic skills to navigate the complex political landscape of the time and making key decisions that will determine the war's outcome.

name: 16 Tiles Mahjong
summary: 16 Tiles Mahjong is a unlicensed adult Mahjong game made by Gamtec for Sega Genesis in 1992.
Appropriately titled 16, this C.H.A.I.N. link may or may not be linked to an incident of occult Welsh origin.

name: 16 Cyber-personalities: Survivors
summary: Inspired by MBTI, this is a fast-paced, top-down arena shooter roguelite where your inner world becomes the battleground. Harness the power of four elemental sprites to fend off the sinister forces lurking in your mind. No matter what your personalities are, you can conquer your darkest thoughts!

name: 16: The Ultimate 15 Puzzle
summary: Prepare to master the power of the cursor in this skill-based puzzle. Move the tiles in the smoothest way possible to put the tiles in position. Improve your record time and analyze your solve in Classic Mode. Discover and practice the drills to become a master in Campaign mode.

name: 16BitSurvivors
summary: 16Bit Survivors is a retro horror horde-survival game with roguelike-elements, where you must annihilate ceaseless waves of monsters. Unlock, upgrade, and forge unbreakable synergies to become godlike against the hordes of demonic creatures coming for your flesh

name: 16x16
summary: See if you can beat your previous score in this relaxing arcade game. Watch out for enemies who wander the maze as you collect points and unlock new costumes from treasure chests.

name: 164: The Relentless Climb
summary: The summit is your sole obsession. But soon, fatigue will yield to the echo of your own thoughts. In this suffocating silence, the summit slips away and doubt becomes your guide. Will you make it through the 164 floors, or are you destined to fall again and again?
